Citation.sAbstract: For separation of the mixtures cyclohexanone and alcohols by distillation, the isobaric vapor-liquid equilibrium (VLE) data for the systems cyclohexanone + (ethanol / n-propanol / isopropanol) were measured at 101.3 kPa by an improved Rose still. The consistency of the experimental VLE data was validated by the Herington, van Ness and pure component consistency test. The NRTL, UNIQUAC and Wilson activity coefficient models were applied to correlate the experimental data, and the binary interaction parameters of the three models were optimized. For comparison, the UNIFAC and COSMO-SAC models were also employed to predict the vapor-liquid equilibrium data for the systems. The predicted results by the UNIFAC and COSMO-SAC models were in an agreement with the experimental VLE data.
Citation.sTitle: Isobaric Vapor-Liquid Phase Equilibrium Measurements, Correlation, and Prediction for Separation of the Mixtures of Cyclohexanone and Alcohols
